&lt;pre&gt;gls.enums.EnumTest &amp;gt; testEnumWithPropertiesAndDanglingComma_GROOVY_7773 FAILED
 org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed:
 TestScript24.groovy: 5: unexpected token: &amp;lt;newline&amp;gt; @ line 5, column 31.
 IN(&apos;Indiana&apos;),
 ^
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16877516" author="paulk" created="Wed, 3 Jul 2019 06:11:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed the issue and merged into master as well. You probably weren&apos;t noticing the error on the master branch since it turns out we run that test only on the new grammar. We could run the test with both grammars but since we tend to phase out antlr2 for Groovy 4, I don&apos;t think it is needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
